{"id":14880902,"mediaExerciseId":"6691c9bb-189b-47bf-b244-a147335b1e4c","exerciseName":"4","chapterName":"5","chapterTitle":"Introduction to Valuation:The Time Value of Money","groupId":612293,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":147,"solutions":[{"id":6062367,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we need to compute the Interest Rate for the given cases. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"We can calculate the Interest Rate using the Present Value (PV) formula. We need to rearrange it to obtain the rate.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\nPV &=\\frac{FV}{(1+r)^t}\\\\\n\\\\\nr &=\\sqrt[t]{\\frac{FV}{PV}}-1\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n*Where:*\n\n- FV is the future value\n- r is the interest rate\n- t is the times the rate is applied\n\n\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"We need to use the values provided in the table for each case:\n\n*r1*\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned} \nr &=\\sqrt[5]{\\frac{\\$317}{\\$181}}-1\\\\\n&=\\boxed{11.86\\%}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe rate in case 1 is **11.86%**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"*r2*\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\nr &=\\sqrt[17]{\\frac{\\$1,080}{\\$335}}-1\\\\\n&=\\boxed{7.13\\%}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe rate in case 2 is **7.13%**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"*r3*\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned} \nr &=\\sqrt[13]{\\frac{\\$185,382 }{\\$48,000}}-1\\\\\n&=\\boxed{10.95\\%}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe rate in case 3 is **10.95%**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"*r4*\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned} \nr &=\\sqrt[30]{\\frac{\\$531,618 }{\\$40,353}}-1\\\\\n&=\\boxed{8.97\\%}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe rate in case 4 is **8.97%**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"These are the rates in each case.\n| | | \n|--|--| \nr1\t|11.86%\nr2\t|7.13%\nr3\t|10.95%\nr4\t|8.97%","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"4936b9c1-41d9-40a4-8d3b-3491450fc950","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":7}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880903,"exerciseName":"5","page":147,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"49fb1ee8-9b41-446f-8eaa-101ebd8a4a70","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-5-questions-and-problems-5-49fb1ee8-9b41-446f-8eaa-101ebd8a4a70"},{"id":14880904,"exerciseName":"6","page":147,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"8a3bf126-4ad2-409f-acd2-51bbf608dc23","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-5-questions-and-problems-6-8a3bf126-4ad2-409f